An internally displaced person (IDP) has tested positive to the coronavirus pandemic after leading funeral prayer of the Borno first Index case, the late MSF nurse. Making the disclosure Friday evening during the daily media briefings for the COVID-19, the secretary, Borno State High Powered Response Team for the Control and Prevention of COVID-19, who is also the state’s Commissioner for Health, Dr. Saliyu Kwaya-bura, said the IDP is from the Bakassi IDPs camp. He, however, said that the IDP had been taken to isolation centre where he was being monitored, adding that he was responding positively. Kwaya-bura added that so far the state had recorded additional three cases bringing total cases that have tested positive to 15 in addition to the two index cases that died. He said the state government is doing everything within its reach to ensure that all contacts to the index cases are traced. On protective measures for the health workers in the state, the commissioner said, government has provided good working conditions for the health workers, adding the state is paying daily allowances to encourage the health workers amid the risk. In his remarks, the commissioner for Home Affairs, Information and Culture, Hon. Babakura ABBA-Jato said the state was considering relaxing the lockdown for one or two days for Ramadan. 